Class Death

  • java.lang.Object
    • pec.Event
      • event.Event_Simulation
        • event.Event_Individual
          • event.Death
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<IEvent>, IEvent

    public class Death
extends Event_Individual
    Death is the class that extends the Event_Individual abstract class and has the purpose of distinguish different types of events. A Death object encapsulates the information needed to process the corresponding event and a corresponding execute method. This information includes:
    • The time of the event;
    • The Individual associated with the event;
    • The simulation in which the event was generated.
    Author:
    Marta Marques (80882), Pedro Direita (81305), Jose Fernandes (82414)
